<figureCitation box="[1007,1111,692,718]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStartId-0="2.[136,229,1921,1943]" captionStartId-1="3.[136,229,1860,1882]" captionTargetBox-0="[178,1406,199,1893]" captionTargetBox-1="[167,1426,209,1819]" captionTargetId-0="figure-17@2.[177,1410,187,1893]" captionTargetId-1="figure-18@3.[151,1436,190,1836]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. Ardisia pyrotechnica Julius, Tagane &amp; Utteridge. A Flowering branch showing inflorescence subtended by two large foliose bracts. B Inflorescence, close up. C Mature flower, fully anthesis and floral bract. D Mature flower, partially at anthesis. E Flower dissected to show the stamen arrangement. F Calyx-lobes, showing the adaxial (right) and abaxial surface (left). G Stamen and pistil. H Anther, adaxial (right) and abaxial (left) surface. I Ovary dissected to show the ovules. J Main stem apex showing arrangement of leaves and lateral branch. K The details of venation and glands on the abaxial surface of lamina. Illustration by Mohamad Aidil Nordin." captionText-1="FIGURE 2. Ardisia pyrotechnica Julius, Tagane &amp; Utteridge. A Habit showing the leaves and flowering branches arrangement on the stem. B Inflorescence subtended two large foliose bracts. C Flower, close-up, adaxial view. D Flower, close-up, abaxial view. Images by Shuichiro Tagane." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5425675" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5425677" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5425675/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5425677/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="206">Figs. 1‒2</figureCitation>
