<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,768,1042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="206">
Among the Bornean members of subgenus (§) 
<taxonomicName authority="Hübner" box="[580,647,768,789]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pyrgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subgenus" subGenus="Pyrgus">
<emphasis box="[580,647,768,789]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="206">Pyrgus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the new species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merrill" authorityYear="1929" box="[981,1166,768,789]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="1" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="breviramea">
<emphasis box="[981,1166,768,789]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="206">Ardisia breviramea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having large foliose bracts, being hairy on inflorescences and the pinkish-white flowers, but 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius, Tagane &amp; Utteridge" authorityName="Julius, Tagane &amp; Utteridge" authorityYear="2021" box="[813,964,804,825]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="1" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyrotechnica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[813,828,804,825]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="206">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[840,964,804,825]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="206">pyrotechnica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs especially in the massive inflorescences up to 
<quantity box="[214,273,840,862]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="1" pageNumber="206" unit="cm" value="26.0">26 cm</quantity>
long and branched to 3 orders (vs. 
<quantity box="[611,658,840,861]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="206" unit="cm" value="8.0">8 cm</quantity>
long and to 2 orders in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merrill" authorityYear="1929" box="[886,1022,840,861]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="1" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="breviramea">
<emphasis box="[886,901,840,861]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="206">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[912,1022,840,861]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="206">breviramea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the larger sepals up to 
<quantity box="[1257,1324,840,861]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="206" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
long, elliptic to narrowly elliptic and slightly overlapping at base (rather than smaller, 
<quantity box="[893,990,876,898]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.25" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="206" unit="mm" value="5.25" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.5">4.5–6 mm</quantity>
long, oblong-elliptic and not overlapping at the base in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merrill" authorityYear="1929" box="[263,399,912,933]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="1" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="breviramea">
<emphasis box="[263,278,912,933]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="206">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[289,399,912,933]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="206">breviramea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
