<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="209" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,1372]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,353,554,580]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Discussion:—</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mez, C." box="[353,485,554,581]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" pagination="1 - 473" refId="ref3652" refString="Mez, C. (1902) Myrsinaceae. In: Engler, A. (Ed.) Das Pflanzenreich, Heft 9, IV. Fam. 236. Verlag von Wilhelm Engelmann, Leipzig, pp. 1 - 473." type="book chapter" year="1902">Mez (1902)</bibRefCitation>
classified 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swartz" authorityYear="1788" box="[607,688,554,580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[607,688,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Ardisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into 14 subgenera, and an additional two subgenera were proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stone, B. C." box="[172,314,590,616]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" pagination="276 - 294" refId="ref3887" refString="Stone, B. C. (1993) New and noteworthy Malesian Myrsinaceae, VI. Scherantha, a new subgenus of Ardisia. Pacific Science 47 (3): 276 - 294." type="journal article" year="1993">Stone (1993</bibRefCitation>
: § 
<emphasis box="[339,467,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Scherantha</emphasis>
) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Larsen, K. &amp; Hu, C. M." box="[533,759,590,617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" pagination="161 - 162" refId="ref3470" refString="Larsen, K. &amp; Hu, C. M. (1995) Reduction of Tetrardisia to Ardisia. Nordic Journal of Botany 15: 161 - 162. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1756 - 1051.1995. tb 00134. x" type="journal article" year="1995">Larsen &amp; Hu (1995</bibRefCitation>
: § 
<taxonomicName box="[784,906,590,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Tetrardisia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[784,906,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Tetrardisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) using the characters of habit, leaf morphology, disposition of flowers at inflorescence branch apices (racemes, umbels, corymbs), inflorescence position and floral morphology. Of these, eleven subgenera are present in 
<collectingCountry box="[763,852,662,688]" name="Malaysia" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Malesia</collectingCountry>
with ten in Borneo (see Stone 1982 for a discussion and key to the groups in 
<collectingCountry box="[414,506,698,724]" name="Malaysia" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Malesia</collectingCountry>
; and 
<bibRefCitation author="Julius, A. &amp; Kajita, T. &amp; Utteridge, T. M. A." box="[565,756,698,725]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" pagination="139 - 148" refId="ref3314" refString="Julius, A., Kajita, T. &amp; Utteridge, T. M. A. (2020) Two new species of Ardisia subgenus Tetrardisia (Primulaceae-Myrsinoideae) from Borneo. PhytoKeys 145: 139 - 148. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / phytokeys. 145.48573" type="journal article" year="2020">
Julius 
<emphasis box="[637,686,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
for a key to species of § 
<taxonomicName box="[1031,1153,698,724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Tetrardisia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1031,1153,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Tetrardisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); the genus is species-rich in northern Borneo and the subgeneric classification is fundamental to identification of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swartz" authorityYear="1788" box="[1119,1200,734,760]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1119,1200,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Ardisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in this region. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyrotechnica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Ardisia pyrotechnica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to § 
<taxonomicName box="[437,515,771,796]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pyrgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[437,515,771,796]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Pyrgus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of the terminal inflorescence on a specialized lateral branch below the indeterminate primary axis, which arise directly from the stem (i.e., not axillary) and are leafless except for the bracts subtending the inflorescence; in addition, the lateral branches emerge between two contracted spirally arranged leaves on the stem. The inclusion of this new species within § 
<taxonomicName box="[740,818,879,904]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pyrgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[740,818,879,904]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Pyrgus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been confirmed in the phylogenetic study by the first author [see 
<bibRefCitation author="Julius, A." box="[267,398,914,940]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" refId="ref3286" refString="Julius, A. (2019) Evolution of leaf nodulation in Myrsinoideae (Primulaceae). PhD dissertation, Chiba University, Japan, 116 pp." type="book" year="2019">Julius 2019</bibRefCitation>
, identified as 
<taxonomicName box="[554,674,914,941]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[554,635,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Ardisia</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
vel 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merrill" authorityYear="1929" box="[722,895,914,940]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="breviramea">
aff. 
<emphasis box="[767,895,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">breviramea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sample no. 603)].
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,1372]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">
Although the pinkish-white flowers and relatively longer sepals of 
<taxonomicName box="[958,1194,950,976]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyrotechnica">
<emphasis box="[958,1194,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Ardisia pyrotechnica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resemble the Bornean species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merrill" authorityYear="1929" box="[228,391,986,1013]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="breviramea">
<emphasis box="[228,391,986,1013]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">A. breviramea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the two taxa are unlikely to be confused. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merrill" authorityYear="1929" box="[904,1125,986,1012]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="breviramea">
<emphasis box="[904,1125,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Ardisia breviramea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was formerly assigned into § 
<emphasis box="[150,269,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Acrardisia</emphasis>
by Stone (1989: 270) in his checklist to Bornean species, but is a member of § 
<taxonomicName box="[1149,1227,1023,1048]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pyrgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1149,1227,1023,1048]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Pyrgus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having the terminal inflorescences on specialized lateral branches etc. The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merrill" authorityYear="1929" box="[1026,1242,1058,1084]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="breviramea">
<emphasis box="[1026,1242,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Ardisia breviramea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in several features including the inflorescence size and sepal morphology listed in the diagnosis, but also several other characters: the elliptic leaves with shorter petioles up to 
<quantity box="[597,652,1130,1157]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" unit="cm" value="3.0">3 cm</quantity>
long (vs. ovate-lanceolate to elliptic or oblanceolate leaves with longer petioles up to 
<quantity box="[293,369,1166,1193]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" unit="cm" value="5.5">5.5 cm</quantity>
long in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merrill" authorityYear="1929" box="[461,620,1166,1193]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="breviramea">
<emphasis box="[461,620,1166,1193]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">A. breviramea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), an acuminate leaf apex (rather than acute to usually acuminate-caudate), arcuate lateral veins joining near the margin (vs. arcuate but not joining), corolla lobes sparsely brown lineate on the upper part (but densely so throughout in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merrill" authorityYear="1929" box="[652,813,1238,1265]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="breviramea">
<emphasis box="[652,813,1238,1265]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">A. breviramea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and only two relatively large foliose bracts below the inflorescence (the inflorescence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merrill" authorityYear="1929" box="[524,682,1274,1301]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="breviramea">
<emphasis box="[524,541,1275,1301]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[554,682,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">breviramea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is subtended by two large and 1 to 4 small foliose bracts). In addition, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merrill" authorityYear="1929" box="[136,299,1310,1337]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="breviramea">
<emphasis box="[136,299,1310,1337]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">A. breviramea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in the north-east region of Borneo, especially around the Tawau region in south-east 
<collectingRegion box="[136,208,1346,1372]" country="Malaysia" name="Sabah" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Sabah</collectingRegion>
.
